Subject: drm/i915: Invoke another _DSM to enable MUX on HP Workstation laptops
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 8e55f99c510f38acb9b1b7552cb942eeb585795e
Patch-mainline: v5.15-rc1
References: jsc#PED-1166 jsc#PED-1168 jsc#PED-1170 jsc#PED-1218 jsc#PED-1220 jsc#PED-1222 jsc#PED-1223 jsc#PED-1225

On HP Fury G7 Workstations, graphics output is re-routed from Intel GFX
to discrete GFX after S3. This is not desirable, because userspace will
treat connected display as a new one, losing display settings.

The expected behavior is to let discrete GFX drives all external
displays.

The platform in question uses ACPI method \_SB.PCI0.HGME to enable MUX.
The method is inside the another _DSM, so add the _DSM and call it
accordingly.

I also tested some MUX-less and iGPU only laptops with that _DSM, no
regression was found.

v4:
 - Rebase.
 - Change the DSM name to avoid confusion.
 - Move the function call to intel_opregion.

v3:
 - Remove BXT from names.
 - Change the parameter type.
 - Fold the function into intel_modeset_init_hw().

v2:
 - Forward declare struct pci_dev.

Closes: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/intel/-/issues/3113
